NAME

      gcloud preview container clusters create - create a cluster for running
         containers

SYNOPSIS

      gcloud preview container clusters create NAME
         [--cluster-api-version CLUSTER_API_VERSION] [--format FORMAT] [--help]
         [--machine-type MACHINE_TYPE, -m MACHINE_TYPE] [--no-healthcheck]
         [--num-nodes NUM_NODES; default="3"] [--password PASSWORD]
         [--project PROJECT] [--quiet, -q] [--source-image SOURCE_IMAGE]
         [--user USER, -u USER; default="admin"] [--zone ZONE, -z ZONE] [-h]

DESCRIPTION

      Create a cluster for running containers.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS

      NAME

         The name of this cluster.

FLAGS

      --cluster-api-version CLUSTER_API_VERSION

         The kubernetes release version to launch the cluster with. Defaults to
         server-specified.

      --machine-type MACHINE_TYPE, -m MACHINE_TYPE

         The type of machine to use for workers. Defaults to server-specified

      --no-healthcheck

         Do not wait for the cluster api to initialize after creation. If set,
         return cluster description as soon as it is created.

      --num-nodes NUM_NODES; default="3"

         The number of nodes in the cluster.

      --password PASSWORD

         The password to use for cluster auth.

      --source-image SOURCE_IMAGE

         The source image to use for workers. Defaults to server-specified

      --user USER, -u USER; default="admin"

         The user name to use for cluster auth.

GLOBAL FLAGS

      --format FORMAT

         Specify a format for printed output. By default, a command-specific
         human-friendly output format is used. Setting this flag to one of the
         available options will serialize the result of the command in the
         chosen format and print it to stdout. Supported formats are: json,
         text, yaml.

      --help

         Display detailed help.

      --project PROJECT

         The Google Cloud Platform project name to use for this invocation. If
         omitted then the current project is assumed.

      --quiet, -q

         Disable all interactive prompts when running gcloud commands. If input
         is required, defaults will be used, or an error will be raised.

      --zone ZONE, -z ZONE

         The zone (e.g. us-central1-a) for the cluster

      -h

         Print a summary help and exit.

NOTES

      This command is in the Google Cloud SDK preview component. See installing
      components if it is not installed.

